<AbstractNarration>Computer Science (31)&lt;br/&gt;Intellectual Merit: The Teaching Computer Networks through Simulation Experiments and Animation Library (NET-SEAL) project is creating curriculum materials which are&lt;br/&gt;enabling undergraduates to experiment with computer networks.  Using NET-SEAL,&lt;br/&gt;students are creating network simulations which use animation to visualize the&lt;br/&gt;dynamics of the network protocols.  Through a collaboration with a two-year&lt;br/&gt;college, the project is addressing the needs of two-year college curriculums by&lt;br/&gt;expanding the simulation support to include popular commercial networking&lt;br/&gt;components. NET-SEAL engages students with dynamic animations and provides an&lt;br/&gt;experimental environment which promotes learning-by-doing.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Broader Impact: NET-SEAL is being distributed by a commercial publisher as&lt;br/&gt;a supplement to a widely used undergraduate networking textbook.</AbstractNarration>
